WEBVTT

00:00.334 --> 00:02.768
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

00:02.770 --> 00:04.770
Olivia: I'm fine.
Jake: I don't think you are.

00:04.772 --> 00:06.906
I'm fine.

00:06.907 --> 00:09.041
It's been two days.
Are you talking to somebody?

00:09.043 --> 00:11.276
You need to talk about it,
what happened to you,

00:11.278 --> 00:13.012
To someone.

00:13.014 --> 00:15.147
You need a...War buddy.

00:15.149 --> 00:19.151
Even the biggest, baddest
navy seals have war buddies.

00:19.153 --> 00:22.187
I'm not there --
at the talking stage.

00:22.189 --> 00:25.224
I'm just tired,
so i'm resting.

00:25.226 --> 00:27.159
Resting?
Yes, resting.

00:27.161 --> 00:29.128
Uh-huh, not working?
No.

00:29.130 --> 00:31.764
Look, 'cause you're the kind of
person that would do that...

00:31.766 --> 00:34.299
This is it.
...Dive back into work
like nothing ever happened.

00:34.301 --> 00:39.204
I'm in bed right now,
and i'm pretty sleepy, so...

00:39.206 --> 00:40.305
[ yawns ]

00:40.307 --> 00:41.740
Okay.

00:41.742 --> 00:46.145
If you are resting,
i guess i'll let you go.

00:46.147 --> 00:48.113
I'll call you tomorrow.

00:57.124 --> 00:59.058
[ police radio chatter ]

00:59.060 --> 01:01.126
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:01.128 --> 01:02.795
Connors: Olivia.
Chief connors.

01:02.797 --> 01:05.197
Thanks for coming down.
I heard you weren't available.

01:05.199 --> 01:07.166
Wasn't sure
i'd get you.

01:07.168 --> 01:08.267
What's his name?

01:08.269 --> 01:10.302
Brandon parker, 17.

01:10.304 --> 01:12.071
Matched the description

01:12.073 --> 01:13.839
Of a suspected shoplifter
a couple blocks away.

01:13.841 --> 01:16.108
Officer stops
to question him,

01:16.110 --> 01:18.110
Kid pulls a knife,
officer shoots him --

01:18.112 --> 01:20.212
Well within his rights --
and now we've got

01:20.214 --> 01:23.115
A dead black kid put there
by a white police officer.

01:23.117 --> 01:25.084
You need me to handle
the optics?

01:25.086 --> 01:27.086
I run a clean force.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.087
The last thing i want is a riot
that sets my city on fire.

01:29.090 --> 01:31.824
How long has the body
been here?

01:31.826 --> 01:34.226
Half an hour.
Waiting for the coroner.

01:34.228 --> 01:35.828
The coroner
needs to get here fast.

01:35.830 --> 01:37.546
You need to move
that body

01:37.547 --> 01:39.263
Out of the street
as soon as possible.

01:39.266 --> 01:41.100
We are four short blocks
from the capitol,

01:41.102 --> 01:42.301
Within the shadow
of the white house.

01:42.303 --> 01:44.336
One misstep --
[ gunshot ]

01:44.338 --> 01:47.172
Bring me the cop
who shot my son!

01:54.215 --> 01:57.249
Sir, i need you
to put that down gun.
Connors:
We need some backup down here.

01:57.251 --> 01:59.251
Tell your men
to stand down.
I can't do that.

01:59.253 --> 02:00.853
Chief connors.
Where's mitchell?
Mitchell!

02:00.855 --> 02:03.322
Chief connors.
Widen the perimeter.

02:03.323 --> 02:05.790
Bring me the cop
who shot my son.
Get those gawkers back
as far as possible!

02:05.793 --> 02:07.159
Every one of these bystanders
has a cellphone

02:07.161 --> 02:08.694
With a camera built in.

02:08.695 --> 02:10.228
You shoot that man,
you'll be famous worldwide

02:10.231 --> 02:11.797
In under 10 minutes.

02:11.799 --> 02:13.765
Clarence: I'm not leaving
until you bring me that cop.

02:13.767 --> 02:14.900
Officer: Put the gun down, sir.
Come on, connors.

02:14.902 --> 02:16.301
No!
Lower your weapon -- now!

02:16.303 --> 02:18.237
Sir! Sir!

02:18.239 --> 02:20.305
Mr. Parker!

02:20.307 --> 02:21.840
Name's clarence.

02:21.842 --> 02:22.908
Hi, clarence.

02:22.910 --> 02:24.276
I'm olivia.
I'm here to help you.

02:24.278 --> 02:25.777
I thought we could talk.

02:25.779 --> 02:28.213
Are the one
that killed my son?
No, sir.

02:28.215 --> 02:30.782
Then i don't have anything
to say to you.

02:30.784 --> 02:32.217
I understand
you want answers,

02:32.219 --> 02:34.219
But without access
to the crime scene --

02:34.221 --> 02:35.287
Crime scene?

02:35.289 --> 02:38.157
One of them
murdered my son.

02:38.159 --> 02:40.259
How do you think
cops who murdered my son

02:40.261 --> 02:42.227
Are gonna handle
the crime scene?

02:42.229 --> 02:44.830
The attorney general
of the united states

02:44.832 --> 02:47.550
Is a friend of mine.

02:47.551 --> 02:50.269
If i can get him down here
to oversee the investigation,

02:50.271 --> 02:52.171
Make sure the evidence
stays intact,

02:52.173 --> 02:53.906
Make sure everything's
handled properly,

02:53.908 --> 02:55.908
Is that something
you would be interested in?

02:55.910 --> 02:58.911
You can get the attorney general
of the united states

02:58.913 --> 03:00.812
Down here?
I can.

03:00.814 --> 03:02.214
Who are you?

03:02.216 --> 03:04.183
Olivia pope.

03:04.185 --> 03:06.185
I can get
the attorney general here.

03:06.187 --> 03:08.854
I can, but i need you
to hand over the gun first.

03:08.856 --> 03:09.855
No.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.890
Mr. Parker!

03:13.827 --> 03:15.961
No one gets my gun.

03:17.298 --> 03:19.198
Cop shot a kid.

03:19.200 --> 03:20.899
Father just showed up
with a shotgun,

03:20.901 --> 03:22.935
Won't let the cops near the body
until he talks

03:22.937 --> 03:24.303
To the officer
who killed his son.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.305
You need one of my a.U.S.A.S
down there?

03:26.307 --> 03:27.906
I promised him<i> you,</i>
david.

03:27.908 --> 03:29.775
I'm the attorney general
of the united states.

03:29.777 --> 03:31.910
You can't just promise me
to people.
You need to come down here.

03:31.912 --> 03:33.946
I don't think you understand
how bad this is.

03:33.948 --> 03:36.348
And i don't think you understand
how the law works.

03:36.350 --> 03:37.883
I have a meeting.
David!

03:37.885 --> 03:39.885
[ police radio chatter ]

03:39.887 --> 03:42.988
So, the question is, can we
replace the vice president?

03:42.990 --> 03:44.990
Unfortunately,
the constitution doesn't cover

03:44.992 --> 03:46.858
The incapacitation
of a vice president,

03:46.860 --> 03:48.260
Which leaves you
with two options,

03:48.262 --> 03:49.861
The first of which
is impeachment

03:49.863 --> 03:51.830
For high crimes
and misdemeanors.

03:51.832 --> 03:53.799
We can't impeach him.
How would that look?

03:53.801 --> 03:55.551
With all due respect,
mr. President,

03:55.552 --> 03:57.302
The man did try to overthrow
the united states government.

03:57.304 --> 03:59.304
Which no one would believe
now that he's a pumpkin.

03:59.306 --> 04:00.939
Which leaves
the second option,

04:00.941 --> 04:02.391
Section 2
of the 25th amendment,

04:02.392 --> 04:03.842
Which says that
whenever there's a vacancy

04:03.844 --> 04:04.943
In the vice president's
position,

04:04.945 --> 04:06.245
The president
can fill the post.

04:06.247 --> 04:07.879
We can argue that,

04:07.881 --> 04:09.948
Even though he's alive,
this is essentially a vacancy.

04:09.950 --> 04:11.783
It's a reach,
but i think it's doable.

04:11.785 --> 04:13.352
Then go do it.
Yes, sir.

04:13.354 --> 04:14.987
[ clears throat ]

04:14.989 --> 04:17.823
In terms
of a replacement...

04:17.825 --> 04:21.260
What do you think of
abernathy or bascombe?

04:21.262 --> 04:23.112
[ sighs ]

04:23.113 --> 04:24.963
You promised the world
a bold second term,

04:24.965 --> 04:27.032
Not two more scoops
of vanilla.

04:27.034 --> 04:29.901
I am tired of my vice presidents
trying to overthrow me.

04:29.903 --> 04:31.770
Those two are loyal,
competent --

04:31.772 --> 04:32.904
And as old
as the hills.

04:32.906 --> 04:34.273
They're one cigarette away

04:34.275 --> 04:36.341
From joining andrew
in the stroke ward.

04:36.343 --> 04:38.844
Mellie's next.
I promised her.

04:38.846 --> 04:41.280
She doesn't need
the competition.

04:48.055 --> 04:51.056
Do you know
what an uphill battle

04:51.058 --> 04:53.859
It's going to be
for mellie

04:53.861 --> 04:57.863
To go from being first lady
to being president?

04:57.865 --> 05:00.966
Call bascombe and abernathy.
I want them both vetted.

05:03.037 --> 05:04.936
[ crowd shouting indistinctly ]

05:04.938 --> 05:07.806
Olivia:
There's an awful lot of cops.

05:07.808 --> 05:09.841
We need them
to keep these people back.

05:09.843 --> 05:11.843
It's for their own safety,
olivia.

05:11.844 --> 05:13.844
The man's got a gun.
Yeah, but he's not gonna
shoot them.

05:13.847 --> 05:15.781
These people are his neighbors,
his supporters.

05:15.783 --> 05:17.783
They're the last people
he's interested in hurting.

05:17.785 --> 05:18.950
Can't take any risks.
Ellison: Olivia pope.

05:18.952 --> 05:20.786
Assistant
u.S. Attorney ellison

05:20.788 --> 05:22.321
From the attorney
general's office.

05:22.323 --> 05:24.056
I asked for david rosen.
He sent me.

05:24.058 --> 05:26.925
How can i help?
You can get me david rosen.

05:26.927 --> 05:27.926
He's not available.

05:27.928 --> 05:28.960
Mr. Parker!

05:28.962 --> 05:30.862
Damn it.
Who's that?

05:30.864 --> 05:31.963
Can i come over there?

05:31.965 --> 05:33.065
Neighborhood activist.

05:33.067 --> 05:35.434
He's given us
trouble before.

05:39.840 --> 05:42.341
Olivia: He can't.
Sir, get back here! Sir!

05:42.343 --> 05:44.810
My name is marcus walker.

05:44.812 --> 05:46.812
Sir,
you need to stay back.
I'm using my cellphone

05:46.814 --> 05:49.014
To record everything
that's happening right now.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.849
You will not shoot me!
You cannot shoot me!

05:50.851 --> 05:51.950
You're being recorded!

05:51.952 --> 05:54.119
Get him out of there!
I need to go in.

05:54.121 --> 05:55.988
I can't let you do that,
olivia.

05:55.989 --> 05:57.856
Chief connors, i can take
care of this for you,
but i need to go in.

05:57.858 --> 05:59.825
Tell your men to stand down
and let me go in.

05:59.827 --> 06:03.061
Stand down!

06:03.063 --> 06:05.097
[ indistinct talking ]

06:07.067 --> 06:09.368
Excuse me.

06:09.370 --> 06:11.970
Can i help you?

06:11.972 --> 06:13.905
Marcus walker.
Olivia pope.

06:13.907 --> 06:16.842
I'm sorry,
but you can't be out here.
Mr. Parker is my neighbor.

06:16.844 --> 06:18.143
He drove me home
from the hospital

06:18.145 --> 06:19.845
When i was three days old.

06:19.847 --> 06:21.113
We really need you
back by behind the tape.

06:21.115 --> 06:23.849
I want marcus to stay.

06:23.851 --> 06:26.952
Mr. Parker
wants me to stay.

06:26.954 --> 06:29.821
Okay.

06:29.823 --> 06:31.089
Mr. Parker,
i called in that favor.

06:31.091 --> 06:32.380
See that woman
down there?

06:32.381 --> 06:33.670
She's with
the justice department.

06:33.671 --> 06:34.960
She's gonna oversee
the investigation,

06:34.962 --> 06:36.962
Make sure everything is done
by the book.

06:36.964 --> 06:39.831
You said you could get
the attorney general down here.
I know.

06:39.833 --> 06:42.801
I did.
But i spoke with him directly...
Do you mind if i ask
who hired you?

06:42.803 --> 06:44.436
...And ms. Ellison
is authorized to handle this.

06:44.437 --> 06:46.070
You now you have
the support and oversight
of the federal government,

06:46.073 --> 06:48.039
But you're going
to have to put the gun down now.

06:48.041 --> 06:49.975
Let us take your son
out of the street,

06:49.977 --> 06:52.010
Have him looked at
by the medical examiner.

06:52.012 --> 06:53.011
Who hired you?

06:53.013 --> 06:54.880
She's helping me out,
marcus.

06:54.882 --> 06:56.181
Helping you
and cashing a check

06:56.183 --> 06:58.884
From the washington
metro police?

06:58.886 --> 07:01.820
Impressive. What's the going
rate for playing both sides?

07:01.822 --> 07:03.155
I'm working
to defuse the situation,

07:03.157 --> 07:05.157
To get to the bottom
of what happened,

07:05.159 --> 07:08.093
To give mr. Parker what he wants
without any more violence.

07:08.095 --> 07:09.895
Well,
that's your first mistake,

07:09.897 --> 07:11.830
Thinking this situation
needs to be defused.

07:11.832 --> 07:14.900
She's telling you
to trust her,

07:14.902 --> 07:16.968
Yet she couldn't deliver on
the only thing she promised you.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.804
Mr. Parker, put the gun down
and come with me.

07:18.806 --> 07:20.138
That's the only way
this works.

07:20.140 --> 07:22.941
I brought this for you.

07:22.943 --> 07:24.943
Just want you
to be comfortable.

07:24.945 --> 07:27.946
Because if you leave here,
if you put that gun down,

07:27.948 --> 07:29.181
You're giving up
on the only power

07:29.183 --> 07:31.049
You'll ever have
in this situation.

07:31.051 --> 07:34.152
And she wouldn't be here
unless you had lots of power.

07:34.154 --> 07:35.821
I'm not the enemy.

07:35.823 --> 07:37.055
Are you sure?

07:39.960 --> 07:41.059
Mr. Parker.

07:57.010 --> 08:00.979
In case it rains
or something.

08:00.981 --> 08:04.015
I want him
to be protected...

08:04.017 --> 08:05.951
From the elements.

08:08.922 --> 08:11.890
[ crowd murmuring ]

08:13.961 --> 08:15.126
Good for you, baby!

08:15.128 --> 08:16.161
That's right!

08:16.163 --> 08:18.897
[ crowd cheering ]

08:38.952 --> 08:41.019
Marcus:
I said, "can you hear me?"

08:41.021 --> 08:41.920
Crowd: Yes!

08:41.922 --> 08:44.055
Can the dcpd hear us?

08:44.057 --> 08:45.190
Crowd: Yes!

08:45.192 --> 08:48.126
Can the caring,
thoughtful citizens

08:48.128 --> 08:50.128
Of these great united states
hear us?

08:50.130 --> 08:51.863
Crowd: Yes!

08:51.865 --> 08:53.098
Tell me
who i'm dealing with.

08:53.100 --> 08:54.966
Quinn: Marcus walker,
neighborhood activist.

08:54.968 --> 08:57.135
Born and raised in
the rosemead district of d.C.,

08:57.137 --> 08:59.104
Graduated with honors
from georgetown.

08:59.106 --> 09:01.172
Hosts a popular podcast
on civil rights,

09:01.174 --> 09:02.908
Runs a job-placement program

09:02.910 --> 09:04.943
For at-risk kids
in southeast d.C.

09:04.945 --> 09:07.078
We speak
for brandon parker!

09:07.080 --> 09:09.080
And we ask,

09:09.082 --> 09:12.150
When will the people
we pay to protect us

09:12.152 --> 09:15.120
Stop gunning us down
in the streets?!

09:15.122 --> 09:17.055
What about clarence?

09:17.056 --> 09:18.989
Bank clerk for the past 22 years
at rbhayes.

09:18.992 --> 09:21.993
Uh, record clean, taxes paid,
shotgun is registered.

09:21.995 --> 09:24.863
Raised brandon by himself
after his wife, janice,

09:24.865 --> 09:26.965
Died 12 years ago
from breast cancer.

09:26.966 --> 09:29.066
Brandon was supposed to graduate
from high school in june,

09:29.069 --> 09:31.069
Had a part-time job
delivering supplies

09:31.071 --> 09:32.904
For a hardware store
on the hill.

09:32.906 --> 09:36.041
Brandon deserves answers!

09:36.043 --> 09:40.178
His father, clarence,
deserves answers!

09:40.180 --> 09:44.182
We demand answers, too!

09:44.184 --> 09:46.851
Will we leave this corner
without those answers?

09:46.853 --> 09:47.953
Crowd: No!

09:47.955 --> 09:49.120
Let brandon parker
hear you!

09:49.122 --> 09:50.188
Crowd: No!

09:50.190 --> 09:52.891
Stand up!
We fight back!

09:52.893 --> 09:54.893
Stand up! Fight back!

09:54.895 --> 09:56.895
No more black men
under attack!

09:56.897 --> 09:58.863
Crowd:
Stand up! Fight back!

09:58.865 --> 10:00.899
No more black men
