17:55.175 --> 17:56.741
Stand up! Fight back!

17:56.743 --> 17:58.276
No more black men
under attack!

17:58.278 --> 17:59.811
Stand up! Fight back!

17:59.813 --> 18:01.746
No more black men
under attack!

18:01.748 --> 18:03.114
I brought you
a hoagie.

18:03.116 --> 18:05.183
I'm not hungry,
ms. Pope.

18:05.185 --> 18:07.251
[ chanting continues ]

18:21.801 --> 18:23.868
I never let brandon
leave the house

18:23.870 --> 18:25.870
Without saying
where he was going.

18:25.872 --> 18:28.172
I never fell asleep

18:28.174 --> 18:32.743
Until i heard his key
turn in the lock.

18:32.745 --> 18:35.179
No being around girls.

18:35.181 --> 18:39.217
We fought about that one...
A lot.

18:39.219 --> 18:41.285
It may sound
so simple to you,

18:41.287 --> 18:44.755
But i just kept saying
to myself, "get him to 18.

18:44.757 --> 18:46.157
"get him a diploma.

18:46.159 --> 18:49.227
Don't let him end up dead,
locked up."

18:54.167 --> 18:59.804
There was a thrift store
down on browning road.

18:59.806 --> 19:05.176
I used to buy brandon
old portable radios, tvs,

19:05.178 --> 19:07.812
Calculators --

19:07.814 --> 19:10.248
Cheap crap --

19:10.250 --> 19:13.184
'cause he loved
taking stuff apart,

19:13.186 --> 19:14.819
Seeing how it worked.

19:14.821 --> 19:17.889
He always had a mind
for that kind of thing.

19:17.891 --> 19:20.925
He was gonna do
the apprentice thing

19:20.927 --> 19:25.229
After graduation and become
an electrical contractor.

19:25.231 --> 19:28.900
And even though
he wasn't going to college,

19:28.902 --> 19:32.170
I put
a university of maryland sticker

19:32.172 --> 19:34.872
On my truck anyway
so if he ever got pulled over,

19:34.874 --> 19:39.243
The cops wouldn't think
he was just a thug...

19:50.256 --> 19:52.356
[voice breaking]
...Without a f--

19:57.764 --> 19:59.964
Without a future.

20:02.268 --> 20:04.869
All that...

20:04.871 --> 20:06.971
[ breathes deeply ]

20:06.973 --> 20:08.973
And there he is,

20:08.975 --> 20:13.344
Laid out
in the cold street, dead.

20:13.346 --> 20:17.315
We're gonna get
to the bottom of this.

20:17.317 --> 20:20.818
And then you can bury
your son.

20:20.820 --> 20:23.955
That sounds real good,
ms. Pope.

20:23.957 --> 20:28.259
But you and i both know
that this only ends

20:28.261 --> 20:32.296
With me dead or locked up...

20:32.298 --> 20:35.833
'cause that's just the way
things go around here.

20:41.941 --> 20:43.374
[ cellphone chimes ]

20:45.345 --> 20:48.279
Hey, how's it going
down there?

20:48.281 --> 20:49.981
Olivia: Not good.

20:49.983 --> 20:51.816
Do we have footage
of the shooting?

20:51.818 --> 20:53.017
Not yet.
Huck's still on it.

20:53.019 --> 20:54.252
We'll find something.

20:54.254 --> 20:55.853
Call me
as soon as you do.

20:55.855 --> 20:58.923
All press
behind the barricade now.

20:58.925 --> 21:01.025
Quinn,
what are you seeing on tv?

21:01.027 --> 21:02.793
Anything about the protest?

21:02.795 --> 21:05.830
Just something
about the vice president.

21:05.832 --> 21:09.033
[ crowd chanting ]

21:09.035 --> 21:11.269
I got to go.

21:12.272 --> 21:14.005
I know what you're doing
shutting down the press.

21:14.007 --> 21:15.773
We need to separate
the protestors

21:15.775 --> 21:17.008
From the reporters
in order to protect --

21:17.010 --> 21:18.510
Yourselves, right?

21:18.511 --> 21:20.011
So that when you go
into that crowd

21:20.013 --> 21:22.880
Armed with your riot gear
and your tear gas,

21:22.882 --> 21:23.981
The world
won't be watching?

21:23.983 --> 21:25.850
Instead
they'll be focused on, what,

21:25.852 --> 21:27.885
The vice president's stroke --
anything except this?

21:27.887 --> 21:29.820
I hired you
to handle the optics,

21:29.822 --> 21:31.422
And now the optics

21:31.423 --> 21:33.023
Are behind that barricade,
where they belong.

21:33.026 --> 21:34.792
That's what we wanted,
olivia.

21:34.794 --> 21:35.793
That's a good thing.

21:35.795 --> 21:38.829
Whose side
are you on here?

21:38.831 --> 21:39.964
Not yours.

