25:45.878 --> 25:48.112
Your son pulled a knife
on the officer.

25:48.114 --> 25:50.047
Did you see a knife?

25:50.049 --> 25:51.565
I don't.

25:51.566 --> 25:53.082
Then what was he pulling
out of his pocket?

25:53.085 --> 25:54.985
How should i know?

25:54.986 --> 25:56.886
All i know is he doesn't carry
a damn knife.

25:56.889 --> 26:00.858
We can check for a knife.

26:00.860 --> 26:03.260
But we'd have to move
your son.

27:06.192 --> 27:09.927
Let me help you.

27:20.006 --> 27:22.039
He doesn't carry a knife.

27:23.175 --> 27:26.844
Mr. Parker, i think
it might be time to go home.

27:26.846 --> 27:28.846
Grieve your son.

27:28.848 --> 27:31.882
He doesn't carry
a knife.

27:31.884 --> 27:34.852
He doesn't carry a knife!

27:34.854 --> 27:37.087
He doesn't carry a knife!
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Whoa! Mr. Parker!

27:37.089 --> 27:39.857
Get on the ground now!
He doesn't carry a knife!

27:39.859 --> 27:42.159
Lower your weapon now,
or we will be forced to shoot!
Come on, mr. Parker.

27:42.161 --> 27:44.061
He doesn't carry a knife.

27:44.063 --> 27:47.064
No! Do not shoot!

27:47.066 --> 27:50.067
[ police radio chatter ]

27:50.069 --> 27:53.904
This man just needs
some space right now.

27:53.906 --> 27:55.873
Right, mr. Parker?

27:55.875 --> 28:00.010
We're all just gonna give you
some space.

28:00.012 --> 28:05.015
He doesn't carry
a knife.

28:06.852 --> 28:11.055
Marcus and i
are gonna step away now,

28:11.057 --> 28:13.123
And when we do,

28:13.125 --> 28:17.161
I need you
to lower your gun.

28:17.163 --> 28:18.862
Okay?

28:18.864 --> 28:23.167
Can you do that,
mr. Parker?

28:23.169 --> 28:26.236
[ crying ]
nice and slow.

28:26.238 --> 28:31.041
That's it.
That's it.

28:31.043 --> 28:33.210
That's it.

28:46.258 --> 28:50.194
He doesn't carry
a knife!

29:13.018 --> 29:16.019
Officer: The mandatory
curfew is now in effect.

29:16.021 --> 29:20.190
Disperse immediately.
Report to your homes.

29:20.192 --> 29:22.159
Crowd:
Stand up! Fight back!

29:22.161 --> 29:24.928
No more black men
under attack!
[ sighs ]

29:24.930 --> 29:28.098
They're gonna pump these people
full of tear gas.

29:28.100 --> 29:30.868
They'll confront clarence.

29:30.870 --> 29:33.937
If he doesn't surrender,
they'll shoot him.

29:33.939 --> 29:38.142
They just need to be prepared
for what happens after that.

29:38.144 --> 29:40.077
Well, i don't want to think
about it.

29:40.079 --> 29:41.879
I can't watch
the city burn.

29:41.881 --> 29:43.046
Curfew is in effect.

29:43.048 --> 29:45.249
Crowd must disperse immediately.

29:45.251 --> 29:47.017
Reporter:<i> On its second day,</i>

29:47.019 --> 29:48.952
<i>The crowd has grown</i>
<i>both in size and in level...</i>

29:48.954 --> 29:51.021
[ door opens ]
where is she?

29:51.023 --> 29:52.890
Little late
for a drop-in, cy.

29:52.892 --> 29:54.525
Where's mellie?
Why?

29:54.526 --> 29:56.159
Because i just got a call
from the<i> times</i>

29:56.162 --> 29:58.228
Asking for comment
on rosalyn mendez for v.P.

29:58.230 --> 29:59.997
And you think
<i>i</i> leaked it?

29:59.999 --> 30:01.165
You're damn right! I do!

30:01.167 --> 30:03.100
They're digging into her past,
finding dirt.

30:03.102 --> 30:04.535
Well, i didn't.

30:04.536 --> 30:05.969
[ chuckles ]
but she was dirty, cyrus.

30:05.971 --> 30:07.237
It was gonna come out
sooner or later.

30:07.239 --> 30:09.273
Later i could've handled.
Later i would've spun.

30:09.275 --> 30:11.008
But now --
now it's out there.

30:11.010 --> 30:12.943
All right, cy.
Enough.

30:12.945 --> 30:14.979
Mendez is off the table.

30:14.980 --> 30:17.014
I can't sell a v.P.
Who sends her own constituents

30:17.016 --> 30:18.148
To a prison she owns.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.050
We'll deal with it
in the morning!

30:20.052 --> 30:21.285
[ sighs ]

30:28.060 --> 30:29.226
[ sighs ]

30:29.228 --> 30:31.195
I didn't do it.

30:31.197 --> 30:32.229
I know.

30:32.231 --> 30:33.897
[ sighs ]

30:33.899 --> 30:34.898
<i>I</i> did.

30:34.900 --> 30:36.900
And that video

30:36.902 --> 30:39.036
Was a naked power grab
if i've ever seen one.

30:39.038 --> 30:41.905
She'd be just as bad as sally
and andrew, if not worse.

30:41.907 --> 30:46.910
Besides, you were right.
We had a deal.

30:46.912 --> 30:50.180
So...

30:50.182 --> 30:54.017
Let's pick a v.P.
Who won't get in your way.

30:54.019 --> 30:57.020
I have one.

30:57.022 --> 30:58.155
She's perfect.

30:58.157 --> 30:59.957
Competent?

30:59.959 --> 31:03.260
Yes.
And completely unelectable.

31:03.262 --> 31:05.162
This clears newton.

31:05.164 --> 31:06.897
Yeah. Sucks.

31:06.899 --> 31:08.966
How did liv look?
She must be exhausted.

31:08.968 --> 31:11.168
You two let her
go down there?
She's fine.

31:11.170 --> 31:13.904
Fine? She's on the other end
of a grieving dad's shotgun

31:13.906 --> 31:16.073
While pissed-off cops aim a
hundred automatics at his head.

31:16.075 --> 31:17.625
You think
that's a good place

31:17.626 --> 31:19.176
For her to be after
the hell she's been through?

31:19.178 --> 31:20.177
It's liv.

31:20.179 --> 31:21.178
[ key clacks ]

31:21.180 --> 31:23.947
Okay, i don't get this.

31:23.949 --> 31:25.249
Brandon yells at newton,
reaches for something.

31:25.251 --> 31:27.084
Newton opens fire.

31:27.086 --> 31:28.586
Knife found at the scene.

31:28.587 --> 31:30.087
What's that?
Surveillance footing
at the shooting.

31:30.089 --> 31:32.155
Which appears to completely
exonerate the cops,

31:32.157 --> 31:34.124
But they were just sitting
on the tape.

31:34.126 --> 31:35.609
Maybe they were
just holding on to it,

31:35.610 --> 31:37.093
Waiting to release it
when things calm down.

31:37.096 --> 31:39.897
Or maybe they were
hiding something.

31:39.899 --> 31:42.032
All right.
Play it again.

31:42.034 --> 31:44.101
[ crowd shouting indistinctly ]

31:44.103 --> 31:45.135
We found a shadow.

31:45.137 --> 31:46.904
What?
In the back of the cop car

31:46.906 --> 31:48.261
In the bank's
security footage.

31:48.262 --> 31:49.617
I wasn't sure
what i was looking at at first,

31:49.618 --> 31:50.973
So we zoomed in and --
talk faster or say less.

31:50.976 --> 31:52.142
It was a person.

31:52.144 --> 31:53.610
Okay.

31:53.611 --> 31:55.077
Newton made an arrest
an hour before.

31:55.080 --> 31:57.147
There's no record showing
the perp was booked,

31:57.149 --> 31:58.632
But we looked into it
and...

31:58.633 --> 32:00.116
Huck: See that shadow moving
in the backseat?

32:00.119 --> 32:01.151
That's the missing suspect.

32:01.153 --> 32:03.086
The suspect
had a knife.

32:03.088 --> 32:06.957
The knife was never officially
booked into evidence, so...

32:06.959 --> 32:09.059
Crowd: No more black men
under attack!

32:09.061 --> 32:11.094
I think i know
where that knife ended up.

32:11.096 --> 32:12.362
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

32:14.934 --> 32:17.000
Who else knew?

32:17.002 --> 32:18.969
I don't know
what you're talking about.
I'm talking about

32:18.971 --> 32:21.071
The perp in the back seat
of your patrol car --

32:21.073 --> 32:22.706
The one you arrested
last night,

32:22.708 --> 32:25.042
The one whose knife you planted
on brandon parker

32:25.044 --> 32:26.944
When you realized
he was unarmed,

32:26.946 --> 32:29.079
The one you let go
in exchange for his silence.

32:29.081 --> 32:31.014
Was it just you,
or did anyone else

32:31.016 --> 32:33.050
Help you hide the fact
you're a murderer?

32:33.052 --> 32:34.985
I think
you'd better leave.

32:34.987 --> 32:35.953
Or what?

32:35.955 --> 32:37.187
You'll shoot me?

32:42.294 --> 32:44.127
What the hell is this,
chief?

32:44.129 --> 32:46.063
The attorney general,
david rosen.

32:46.065 --> 32:48.298
And these agents are here
to question phillip durant,

32:48.300 --> 32:50.033
The man you picked up
last night.

32:50.035 --> 32:52.069
Then i imagine they'll have
a few questions for you.

32:52.071 --> 32:54.071
We found him
at a convenience store,

32:54.073 --> 32:55.205
Buying lottery tickets.

32:55.207 --> 32:57.007
I guess
he was feeling lucky.

32:57.009 --> 32:58.976
I don't believe this.
You don't want to talk,
that's fine.

32:58.978 --> 33:00.861
We'll use your friend
phillip's testimony.

33:00.862 --> 33:02.745
This is over.
God, what the hell
is it with you people?

33:02.748 --> 33:04.398
"us people"?

33:04.399 --> 33:06.049
Yeah, you people --
i didn't misspeak.

33:06.051 --> 33:08.051
You people have no idea

33:08.053 --> 33:09.720
What loyalty is,
what respect is.

33:09.722 --> 33:12.122
You're here because
you were supposed to help us,

33:12.124 --> 33:14.725
And you spent every second of it
trying to tear us down,

33:14.727 --> 33:16.259
Tear me down,
push your own damn agenda!

33:16.261 --> 33:18.028
I'm here to find
the truth!

33:18.030 --> 33:19.580
The truth is,

33:19.581 --> 33:21.131
Those people in rosemead
have no respect

33:21.133 --> 33:22.199
For anything or anyone.

33:22.201 --> 33:23.266
No, they're like you.

33:23.268 --> 33:25.035
They just take
whenever they want,

33:25.037 --> 33:26.737
And they have no problem
turning their backs

33:26.739 --> 33:29.206
On the people who gave it
to them -- people like me,

33:29.208 --> 33:31.174
Who strap on their boots
every day,

33:31.176 --> 33:33.143
Kiss their wife and kids
goodbye,

33:33.145 --> 33:35.278
And trek 40 miles into a city
where everyone,

33:35.280 --> 33:37.014
Including little babies,

33:37.016 --> 33:39.282
Are taught to look at us
like the enemy!

33:39.284 --> 33:42.786
They are taught to question me,
to disobey me,

33:42.788 --> 33:46.056
And still i risk my life
for these people.

33:46.058 --> 33:49.192
Every day for seven years,
i have allowed myself

33:49.194 --> 33:51.128
To be disrespected and hated
by these people,

33:51.130 --> 33:52.796
All to protect them
from themselves.

33:52.798 --> 33:55.065
I mean, all i hear about
on the news are dirty cops,

33:55.067 --> 33:56.266
Cops who shoot
innocent black kids.

33:56.268 --> 33:58.068
It's crap!

33:58.070 --> 34:00.737
There were 84 murders
in this city last year.

34:00.739 --> 34:03.273
Were all of those cops
shooting innocent black boys?

34:03.275 --> 34:04.741
Hell no.

34:04.743 --> 34:07.144
Those were blacks
turning guns on each other,

34:07.146 --> 34:09.813
And yet somehow
<i>i'm</i> the animal!

34:09.815 --> 34:14.251
Brandon parker is dead
because he didn't have respect,

34:14.253 --> 34:16.153
Because those people
out there

34:16.155 --> 34:18.288
Who are chanting
and crying over his body,

34:18.290 --> 34:20.824
They didn't teach him
the right values.

34:20.826 --> 34:23.010
They didn't teach him respect.

34:23.011 --> 34:25.195
He didn't respect me.
He didn't respect my badge.

34:25.197 --> 34:28.198
Questioning my authority
was not his right!

34:28.200 --> 34:30.333
His blood
is not on my hands!

34:43.148 --> 34:47.851
It's just --
i can't believe i'm really here,

34:47.853 --> 34:48.852
The oval office.

34:48.854 --> 34:50.754
I still feel that way,
every day.

34:50.756 --> 34:52.578
Me too.

34:52.579 --> 34:54.401
It's kind of smaller
than i thought it would be,

34:54.402 --> 34:56.224
Though studies have shown
people actually were smaller

34:56.228 --> 34:58.195
Back when the white house
was built.

34:58.197 --> 34:59.830
Researchers
have discovered

34:59.832 --> 35:02.199
That the average height
of an american soldier

35:02.201 --> 35:04.267
During the revolutionary war
was about 5'7",

35:04.269 --> 35:05.836
Though thomas jefferson
was 6'2".

35:05.838 --> 35:07.804
Susan, do you know
why you're here?

35:07.806 --> 35:11.108
I think i can guess,

35:11.110 --> 35:13.743
Which is why i brought
the presentation materials

35:13.745 --> 35:15.145
On my vaccination
proposal.

35:15.147 --> 35:17.214
I also had a few thoughts
on tax reform

35:17.216 --> 35:19.182
That i'd love to discuss
with you,

35:19.184 --> 35:21.251
But we don't have to do it
all tonight.

35:21.253 --> 35:22.786
Susan,
i've asked you here

35:22.788 --> 35:24.221
Because i'd like to offer you
the vice presidency.

35:26.125 --> 35:27.190
What?

35:27.192 --> 35:32.662
The president is asking you
to be his new vice president.

35:35.834 --> 35:36.800
Why?

35:36.802 --> 35:38.301
"why?"

35:38.303 --> 35:41.138
I'm a terrible choice.
I just got elected.

35:41.140 --> 35:42.873
That's why
i'm asking you.

35:42.875 --> 35:44.875
This town has a way
of taking people

35:44.877 --> 35:46.877
And turning them
into politicians.

35:46.879 --> 35:48.311
I don't want
a politician.

35:48.313 --> 35:50.780
But if i were
the vice president

35:50.782 --> 35:53.150
And then something
happened to you...

35:53.152 --> 35:54.184
Then you would be
president.

35:54.186 --> 35:57.254
But i don't want to be
president.

35:57.256 --> 36:01.825
I mean, no offense,
but your job is the worst job

36:01.827 --> 36:02.859
In the entire world.

36:02.861 --> 36:03.860
[ chuckles ]

36:03.862 --> 36:05.262
No, actually,
vice president

36:05.264 --> 36:08.165
Is probably worse
because you don't actually

36:08.167 --> 36:09.933
Get to do anything,
do you?

36:09.935 --> 36:12.169
And i want to
get things done.

36:12.171 --> 36:13.770
There's so much to do --

36:13.772 --> 36:15.939
Not just
on the vaccination front,

36:15.941 --> 36:18.942
But we need a new tax code
and budget reform,

36:18.944 --> 36:20.944
And there's the war
in west angola

36:20.946 --> 36:23.813
And the war right here at home,
five minutes away.

36:23.815 --> 36:26.066
Have you seen it on tv?

36:26.067 --> 36:28.318
That poor man whose son
was shot dead in the street.

36:28.320 --> 36:31.821
Oh, my god.

36:31.823 --> 36:33.957
If anything like that
ever happened to casey,

36:33.959 --> 36:35.642
My daughter -- she's 10.

36:35.643 --> 36:37.326
If anything like that
ever happened to her --

36:37.329 --> 36:39.896
But of course she's white
and the daughter of a senator,

36:39.898 --> 36:41.865
So the police
are actually gonna think twice

36:41.867 --> 36:42.966
Before shooting her.

36:42.968 --> 36:44.868
But that poor man,

36:44.870 --> 36:47.304
He raised that boy
all by himself.

36:47.306 --> 36:50.941
Can you even imagine what
he is going through right now?

36:50.943 --> 36:52.809
I can't.
I would die.

36:52.811 --> 36:54.978
I would literally die
on the spot.

36:54.980 --> 36:56.279
I would
have to kill myself.

36:56.281 --> 36:57.881
Oh, my gosh.

36:57.883 --> 37:01.351
Oh, my gosh,
i'm so sorry.

37:01.353 --> 37:03.787
Of course you know.

37:03.789 --> 37:08.225
Of course you do.
You know more than anyone.

37:08.227 --> 37:09.826
See?

37:09.828 --> 37:12.963
This is why you don't want me
to be vice president.

37:12.965 --> 37:17.867
I'm terrible at this,
at talking to people

37:17.869 --> 37:20.337
And not saying
what i'm thinking at all times.

37:20.339 --> 37:22.239
I think
we could probably use

37:22.241 --> 37:23.940
A little more of that
around here.

37:23.942 --> 37:25.642
Now [claps hands]

37:25.643 --> 37:27.343
Tell me about
this vaccination plan of yours.

37:27.346 --> 37:31.848
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

37:31.850 --> 37:34.351
David:
Tonight, officer jeffrey newton

37:34.353 --> 37:37.287
Was arrested
for altering evidence,

37:37.289 --> 37:39.856
Perjury,
and filing a false report.

37:39.858 --> 37:42.325
He and fellow officer
edward brennan

37:42.327 --> 37:46.930
Have also been charged with
conspiracy to obstruct justice.

37:46.932 --> 37:48.965
In light of these charges,

37:48.967 --> 37:51.001
The justice department,
under my supervision

37:51.003 --> 37:52.869
And with the full cooperation

37:52.871 --> 37:54.971
Of metro police chief
lawrence connors,

37:54.973 --> 37:57.841
Will open an independent
federal investigation

37:57.843 --> 37:59.976
Into the washington, d.C.,
police force.

37:59.978 --> 38:02.912
But even given these actions,
i don't stand up here

38:02.914 --> 38:05.048
Pretending justice
has been served tonight.

38:05.050 --> 38:09.052
Brandon parker
is still gone.

38:09.054 --> 38:14.024
¶ ...Who put me here ¶

38:14.026 --> 38:16.893
This is what brandon
was reaching for.

38:16.895 --> 38:20.797
This is what
was in his pocket --

38:20.799 --> 38:25.869
The receipt
for his new cellphone.

38:25.871 --> 38:30.774
You were right.
He didn't have a knife.

38:30.776 --> 38:33.843
He had a piece of paper.

38:35.814 --> 38:40.817
The officer who shot your son
is behind bars.

38:40.819 --> 38:46.423
¶ i shall be released ¶

38:51.063 --> 38:54.064
¶ they say ev'ry man
needs protection ¶

38:58.970 --> 39:03.406
¶ they say ev'ry man must fall ¶

39:06.945 --> 39:11.448
¶ so i swear
i see my reflection ¶

39:15.087 --> 39:20.924
¶ somewhere inside these walls ¶

39:22.928 --> 39:27.797
¶ i see my light come shinin' ¶

39:27.799 --> 39:30.867
No one is going to arrest you,
mr. Parker.

39:32.904 --> 39:34.371
Let's go.

39:34.373 --> 39:40.009
¶ from the west unto the east ¶

39:40.011 --> 39:48.151
¶ any day now, any day now ¶

39:48.153 --> 39:55.091
¶ i shall be released ¶

39:58.864 --> 40:00.130
Where are we going?

40:00.132 --> 40:02.899
This isn't my neighborhood.

40:02.901 --> 40:04.901
¶ yonder stands a man
in this lonely crowd ¶

40:04.903 --> 40:08.004
No, it's not.

40:08.006 --> 40:11.141
¶ man who says
he's not to blame ¶

40:14.179 --> 40:17.046
¶ all day long i hear him
hollerin' so loud ¶

40:17.048 --> 40:23.052
David:
Tonight, a young man's potential
was cut tragically short.

40:23.054 --> 40:26.089
Another american community
is looking for answers,

40:26.091 --> 40:28.825
And another father is knowing

40:28.827 --> 40:31.928
The unbearable pain
of losing a child.

40:31.930 --> 40:34.898
Jack, please.
Give us a moment.

40:36.835 --> 40:38.868
Mr. Parker.

40:38.870 --> 40:41.938
I am so sorry
for your loss.

40:41.940 --> 40:44.140
Please...

40:44.142 --> 40:48.144
Call me clarence.

40:48.146 --> 40:53.149
My son's name was...

40:53.151 --> 40:55.985
Brandon.

40:55.987 --> 40:58.087
[ sobbing ]

40:58.089 --> 41:01.124
¶ i shall be released ¶

41:07.866 --> 41:11.167
¶ yonder stands a man
in this lonely crowd ¶

41:11.169 --> 41:14.070
Ours is a country of laws,

41:14.072 --> 41:17.807
But those laws
failed brandon parker tonight.

41:17.809 --> 41:20.009
And i can only hope
in the weeks ahead,

41:20.011 --> 41:22.078
We can begin
to understand why.

41:22.080 --> 41:28.885
¶ all day long i hear him
hollerin' so loud ¶

41:28.887 --> 41:34.958
¶ just cryin' out
that he's not to blame ¶

41:34.960 --> 41:41.064
¶ i see my light come shinin' ¶

41:44.102 --> 41:52.208
¶ from the west unto the east ¶

41:52.210 --> 42:02.819
¶ any day now, any day now ¶

42:02.821 --> 42:08.191
¶ i shall be ¶

42:08.193 --> 42:21.170
¶ released ¶

42:22.140 --> 42:24.107
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]
